        <td bgcolor='black' valign='top' width='100%'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Back when I specialized in Conjuration, Shock of Poison was our main DD spell, there was no epic snare, and pets were conjuration based... seemed like a good choice at the time.</P><P>I remember VI stating that spell specializations did NOT save mana when cast, it only improved the chance of not getting a fizzle...</P><P>Times change... and I have taken a few breaks...  I have noticed some Necros mention that spell specialization actually saves mana on the spell line you specialize in... is this true?  </P><P>I might have missed this change, or maybe I just had a misunderstanding.  I have considered doing the Sol Temple quest to change it... just wanted to get some feedback on you guys on the benefits of Specialization (if any).</P><P>Thanks...</P><P>Xuraz Xorthexia - <BR>Warlock<BR>Xegony Server</P><P>"They call us walking corpses, unholy living dead.<BR>They had to lock us up, put us in their pretty jails." - The Misfits</P><P>Edited by - Xuraz on 08/12/2002  14:50:52</font></td>
