 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Ancagalon</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Add up the total mana you would use in a typical fight. Your specialization should cover the mana you use the most of, most of the time. Root-DOTing, most grouping and definately raiding you are using massivly more ALT then CON. About the only time you might be using more CON is fear kiting, where you are letting your pet do all the work, as darkness costs more then fear. But, in that fear kite, add in a DOT or a lifetap, and ALT is your biggest skill again. </P><P>It would be pretty hard to make the CON specialization argument with a few raw numbers stairing back at you. Do the quest and take the time to max ALT specialization out bud. You will be thankful in the long run. </P><P>Cheers,<BR>Ancagalon the Black<BR>Warlock - Terris Thule</P><P> </font></td>
