        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> There was a time a while ago when specializing Conjuration was a somewhat reasonable alternative to Alteration, since it not only covers Pets and Darkness but also the Poison and Disease DOTs.  And corpse summoning, for that matter.  If you use those really heavily for some reason, keeping Conjuration might be worth it.  Maybe.</P><P>Alteration covers pretty much everything else that's useful, though.  I went Alteration myself.</P><P>I believe that doing the Solusek Ro quest resets everything down to 50, so you'd only need to cast a few Alterations right away until it hits 51 to lock it in.  (Chain cast Shadow Step, that's always fun in a building filled with lava.)</P><P>It might be a while before you notice any significant difference, I'm not sure how long it will take the specialization to get from 50 to 200.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=247832" target="_blank">Morty Undercrypt</a>, Keeper of the <a href="http://www.necrognomicon.com/" target="_blank">NecroGnomicon</a><BR><font size=1>"I am the truth, and the truth shall make you flee."</font id=size1><BR>E'ci</font></td>
